This paper deals with the transmission scheme for a communication channel, specifically the Gaussian broadcast channel with feedback. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of estimators with memory and the analysis of mean square errors suggest a focus on networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The numerical simulations and analysis of achievable rates suggest a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
